1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,540
Hi everyone.

2
00:00:02,480 --> 00:00:05,760
Very soon the Old New Year holiday comes.

3
00:00:06,780 --> 00:00:10,180
As we know, for New Year people decorate the tree.

4
00:00:10,540 --> 00:00:14,200
Well, and CE folks of course decorate the Tesla.

5
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:19,800
The final eighth layer of varnish coating on this product dried.

6
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:25,760
And the moment has come to crown this build with a sphere of a certain diameter.

7
00:00:25,940 --> 00:00:33,880
I decided on the sphere dimensions in advance and got them in stores selling tree decorations.

8
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:37,200
Such plastic spheres.

9
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:42,080
By the way, the boom of New Year sales has passed.

10
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:55,620
And if before the holidays a couple of such beauties cost 220 rubles, now they sell them at the marked-down cost of 49 rubles per pair.

11
00:00:56,420 --> 00:01:01,800
And that's the lucky moment to stock up on such products for the next year.

12
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:09,900
To make an isolated capacity for the Tesla transformer we need precisely one of these plastic spheres.

13
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:20,720
Nichrome wire on the order of 30-40 cm with a cross-section of about one and a half millimeters in diameter.

14
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:25,900
A small brush mandatory with a wooden handle.

15
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:29,600
A plastic dowel.

16
00:01:31,380 --> 00:01:36,260
A hacksaw with a small metal blade.

17
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:43,420
And the main moment — you need to get such tape.

18
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:46,720
Called thermal tape for sauna bath.

19
00:01:47,620 --> 00:01:54,720
It's made on the basis of natural aluminum tape, coated with an adhesive layer.

20
00:01:55,540 --> 00:02:02,380
We'll apply it from its inner side onto the surface of the tree decoration.

21
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:19,320
You should pay attention that there are similar tapes that have approximately the same color and are used for gluing substrates under heated floors.

22
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:23,960
There that tape only has a coating.

23
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:29,740
We need to choose precisely a natural aluminum plate.

24
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:34,340
It should be looked at in the store before purchase.

25
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:47,260
In my opinion, from practice, aluminum is the most suitable metal for surfaces that'll work with static potential.

26
00:02:48,180 --> 00:02:55,200
To start, we should remove the upper part of the sphere.

27
00:02:56,500 --> 00:03:10,980
I picked the dowel nail by diameter so it'd enter exactly this surface — the one that's provided as the limiter for wall entry.

28
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:14,400
It should plug this hole.

29
00:03:17,980 --> 00:03:26,240
Cut this part with the help of a hacksaw and clean the joining places on the surface if there are some bumps.

30
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:33,380
Around the circumference here they're absent, but they should be cut here with a utility knife.

31
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:43,010
I remove the bumps on the sphere's surface.

32
00:03:48,390 --> 00:03:54,470
And the cut spot should also be cleaned.

33
00:04:20,350 --> 00:04:26,350
Now I move to installation of the plastic part from the dowel nail.

34
00:04:27,010 --> 00:04:28,790
So it fits here for us.

35
00:04:29,950 --> 00:04:34,110
Now we'll glue it with the help of a hot glue gun.

36
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:50,280
Apply enough glue.

37
00:04:52,540 --> 00:04:54,620
The extra part will be cut after.

38
00:04:56,660 --> 00:05:01,260
And carefully install in the center.

39
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:06,870
Like this.

40
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:25,300
Now we should wait several minutes until the glue dries.

41
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,280
The extra part removed after.

42
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:35,020
While the glue was drying I managed to straighten the nichrome.

43
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:51,400
Nichrome has resistance for usual current, and for static, its resistance absolutely doesn't impede movement.

44
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,960
Such an interesting feature.

45
00:05:58,260 --> 00:06:10,300
And on the contrary, the presence of nichrome even helps us get a clearer static potential on the surface.

46
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:20,280
How to say it — it slightly impedes movement of what the classics call electrons.

47
00:06:21,140 --> 00:06:22,900
The potentials for us are big.

48
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:31,240
The conductor of the Tesla coil is copper, so free electrons there are present.

49
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:40,940
And for purposes of stopping them, we use nichrome wire.

50
00:06:41,820 --> 00:06:48,300
I cut the extra glue, now everything's ready for further work.

51
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:55,700
Now I form a peculiar peg at the end of the nichrome wire.

52
00:06:56,840 --> 00:07:03,780
I widen it slightly so it'd enter the dowel nail with force.

53
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:08,920
Bring it to

54
00:07:12,110 --> 00:07:13,410
some stop.

55
00:07:14,550 --> 00:07:24,050
And mark the depth to which the nichrome wire was seated.

56
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:31,160
This distance will be useful for us later.

57
00:07:36,050 --> 00:07:43,370
Further the wire is extracted and put aside for now.

58
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:45,430
Here, to this depth it entered.

59
00:07:48,210 --> 00:07:50,970
I move on to the next stage of work.

60
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:53,630
Now the most interesting.

61
00:07:53,770 --> 00:07:55,990
Wrapping our plastic sphere.

62
00:07:57,730 --> 00:08:01,930
I start the work from the point where we have the dowel nail.

63
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:06,830
Around the circumference, with tension, I lead the tape.

64
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:23,200
Lead it as much as possible along the largest sphere diameter, to come to the same point from which we started.

65
00:08:27,990 --> 00:08:36,050
Reach it like this, and now the extra part can be removed.

66
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:38,850
Carefully extract.

67
00:08:40,610 --> 00:08:47,350
And around the sphere we got such a strip.

68
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:56,140
Now we need a brush, more precisely its wooden handle.

69
00:08:57,140 --> 00:09:06,100
I start smoothing first at the dowel nail, form a bump,

70
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:11,660
go around.

71
00:09:15,620 --> 00:09:31,000
And now when this part is formed, smooth the remaining tape from the middle to the edges with such movements.

72
00:09:57,340 --> 00:10:15,820
First don't go through fully — let the tape take the needed position, and next time already smooth the edges.

73
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:28,860
It's not worth applying a metal object, because there's a big risk of tearing the aluminum coating.

74
00:10:30,340 --> 00:10:34,200
And a smooth wooden object handles this very well.

75
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:48,980
So lay tape around the circumference.

76
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:17,780
Now pass to the edges, press, and

77
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:32,340
that's how we got it.

78
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:42,240
Generally speaking, the 50 mm tape width is slightly wide for this diameter.

79
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:46,580
If it were 40 mm, it'd be ideal, fewer of these folds would be.

80
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:50,620
But they don't affect quality, they smooth very well.

81
00:11:51,360 --> 00:12:00,680
If you need to make a sphere of smaller diameter, then naturally such tape will be wide and should be divided in half.

82
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:06,840
Now apply the next tape perpendicularly around the circumference.

83
00:12:08,780 --> 00:12:14,460
I start applying the second tape also from the area where the dowel nail is.

84
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,340
And lead it around the sphere circumference.

85
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:25,020
Stretch so it adheres tightly.

86
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:30,800
So as not to tear the aluminum film.

87
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:50,810
All the same.

88
00:12:51,610 --> 00:12:58,990
Start from this part, form carefully.

89
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:16,710
And also go from the centers to the edges.

90
00:13:16,890 --> 00:13:19,570
Repeat all the same as with the first tape.

91
00:13:24,270 --> 00:13:26,490
This is how our product looks now.

92
00:13:27,070 --> 00:13:31,270
Now apply film to cover this part.

93
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:41,150
And the subsequent layer is applied perpendicularly around the circumference.

94
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:48,990
Repeated all the same actions, leveled with a wooden smooth object.

95
00:13:48,990 --> 00:13:57,650
And constantly form this part, carefully smoothing after each layer.

96
00:13:58,270 --> 00:14:01,670
Start from here, wrap, return here.

97
00:14:03,170 --> 00:14:04,110
Let's go further.

98
00:14:06,890 --> 00:14:12,470
This is how our product looks after the first layer is fully applied.

99
00:14:13,470 --> 00:14:25,230
The whole sphere is fully wrapped, the perpendicular tape and the tapes that were applied around the circumference are visible.

100
00:14:26,570 --> 00:14:40,870
We need to apply two such full layers, and only then we'll move to introducing into the dowel nail hole the wire that was prepared earlier from nichrome.

101
00:14:41,450 --> 00:14:47,750
We'll need to form a smooth contact from this wire so we'd have good contact in this area.

102
00:14:47,990 --> 00:14:52,570
And then above it only the final third layer will be applied.

103
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:58,170
After 40 minutes of intensive work the second layer is applied.

104
00:14:58,670 --> 00:15:01,910
That's how the hands look — characteristic color from aluminum.

105
00:15:02,910 --> 00:15:07,790
Now we can move to forming the hole for the wire.

106
00:15:08,570 --> 00:15:14,630
For this, form a small depression with the back of the brush.

107
00:15:17,930 --> 00:15:21,070
Now make a hole.

108
00:15:25,620 --> 00:15:32,400
Carefully in the center, and flare it inward with the help of a mandrel.

109
00:15:48,180 --> 00:15:54,400
Now we have the contact diameter of the inner surface.

110
00:15:59,430 --> 00:16:00,830
This is how it looks.

111
00:16:01,090 --> 00:16:07,770
That is, the metal is carefully tucked inside to a depth of about 5 mm.

112
00:16:11,010 --> 00:16:17,050
For the next stage we need to measure the mark we made with the marker.

113
00:16:18,050 --> 00:16:21,230
What length it'll be for us.

114
00:16:21,450 --> 00:16:24,450
The immersion depth comes out to 6.5 cm.

115
00:16:25,970 --> 00:16:34,130
And now we should carefully clean the place of future contact with sandpaper.

116
00:16:36,790 --> 00:16:43,430
Clean it to metallic shine, which I'll do now.

117
00:16:44,430 --> 00:16:59,090
After cleaning, transfer the mark to the wire again and cut off from the sticky aluminum tape a strip about 2 cm wide.

118
00:17:00,370 --> 00:17:03,710
And apply it in the middle of the mark.

119
00:17:04,370 --> 00:17:13,110
We need to form a contact body tightly around the wire.

120
00:17:14,330 --> 00:17:15,130
Form.

121
00:17:16,310 --> 00:17:24,750
This contact body will enter this hole with force for us.

122
00:17:29,610 --> 00:17:38,550
The length will need to be picked experimentally so we get the diameter we need.

123
00:17:47,770 --> 00:17:51,630
Form, carefully compacting the surface,

124
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,500
so the contact is good.

125
00:18:08,870 --> 00:18:13,870
One more such strip and everything will be in order.

126
00:18:21,130 --> 00:18:27,550
Now apply the next, slightly deeper,

127
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:39,100
to form a narrow entrance.

128
00:19:03,930 --> 00:19:05,970
Thus,

129
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:13,160
this will be enough for us.

130
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:39,650
It comes out to such a part — from this side it narrows, and here it maximally widens toward the middle where the mark is.

131
00:19:41,470 --> 00:19:48,090
Lead the wire and insert into the sphere hole.

132
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:55,800
Enters with force.

133
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:20,460
Now with subsequent actions carefully insert deeper into the sphere with the help of a tool.

134
00:20:21,460 --> 00:20:26,740
Like this, it enters with force,

135
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:37,130
this way we provide quality contact.

136
00:20:38,770 --> 00:20:49,270
Everything is in place — now the extra part of the foil should be cut and we move on to the next stage.

137
00:20:50,270 --> 00:21:00,670
I did the trimming, and now I do the final formation of the contact surface.

138
00:21:01,110 --> 00:21:16,530
With such movements of a metal object, carefully press the foil that we applied around the circumference of the nichrome wire diameter.

139
00:21:21,670 --> 00:21:28,550
With this we'll have a good quality contact.

140
00:21:29,450 --> 00:21:30,750
This is how it looks.

141
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:44,700
The second stage of work is finished, now we move on to applying the third layer.

142
00:21:45,420 --> 00:21:52,220
The third layer — its start will also be from this side, but will be placed on the wire.

143
00:21:52,920 --> 00:22:01,040
And a kind of bump is formed that'll additionally go around the wire body in this part.

144
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:06,940
This is how the start of the third layer looks.

145
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:14,520
Lead in, go around the wire, and do the forming.

146
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:34,620
We ultimately need to form such a thin tail after all the layers around the wire, which ultimately will be crimped with heat shrink.

147
00:22:36,860 --> 00:22:42,940
The sequence of actions is the same — crosswise and then one layer around the circumference.

148
00:22:42,940 --> 00:22:45,800
And with this the work will be finished.

149
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:56,300
After an hour and a half of continuous work, I finally finished making the isolated capacity for the Tesla transformer.

150
00:22:57,600 --> 00:23:00,860
This is how our sphere ultimately looks.

151
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:08,480
Of course it'll yield slightly in parameters to a solid-metal polished sphere.

152
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:19,440
But it greatly surpasses all kinds of beer cans, heat sinks, transistors, and other things people hook there instead of an isolated capacity.

153
00:23:20,940 --> 00:23:29,660
It has quite a good spherical form, has good contact with the nichrome wire.

154
00:23:29,660 --> 00:23:35,210
Now regarding the sizes of such products.

155
00:23:36,660 --> 00:23:46,500
People usually make Tesla transformers to get various light-noise effects.

156
00:23:46,500 --> 00:24:00,700
And in the layman's head, the idea is firmly entrenched that the Tesla transformer is exactly the resonance transformer that forms long discharges similar to lightning.

157
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:09,780
It can play melodies and other things, but to the Tesla transformer this has no relation.

158
00:24:09,780 --> 00:24:29,080
Because as soon as you get a phyton-like discharge, corona, or some other breakdown, know that you're uselessly spending energy in vain, if that wasn't your goal.

159
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:33,060
The real Tesla transformer doesn't work that way.

160
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:37,200
During its work no streamers are observed.

161
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:40,340
The Tesla coil works in a completely different mode.

162
00:24:41,420 --> 00:25:00,460
There's such an interesting moment, that to start the processes of interaction of the Tesla transformer with the surrounding environment — in particular the air it's located in — you need to charge the surface of this sphere to a static potential of 3.73 kV.

163
00:25:00,460 --> 00:25:15,260
In the area of this voltage, interesting processes start to happen when the Tesla coil draws in ionized and charged particles from the surrounding air.

164
00:25:15,580 --> 00:25:23,580
In such a mode we can use the Tesla transformer for making our CE devices.

165
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:27,360
On this I finish the video.

166
00:25:27,980 --> 00:25:31,240
Remember these few rules.

167
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:38,320
By the way, such a making method as I described, I haven't seen anywhere yet.

168
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:43,560
Possibly someone originally came up with such a method.

169
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:48,580
So use it, the method is very good.

170
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:54,700
And here one more small moment before I forget, about that voltage of 3.73 kV.

171
00:25:55,000 --> 00:26:10,940
You need to understand that the bigger the size of your sphere, the more energy you'll need to pump into the Tesla transformer to charge it to this potential, until the Tesla transformer reaches operating mode.

172
00:26:10,940 --> 00:26:18,180
So if you use big spheres, your Tesla transformer will consume much more.

173
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:29,340
Of course there's also a certain moment with surface area where charge can fit.

174
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:38,940
But we have such a dependency — at 1 kV, say a certain amount, and we can't place more here.

175
00:26:38,940 --> 00:26:49,860
And if we raise the voltage, say to 10 kV, then here the density of charge accumulation on the same surface rises by multiple times.

176
00:26:50,460 --> 00:26:56,020
So in our case we need to chase not geometry, but raising potential.

177
00:26:57,260 --> 00:27:03,940
And not allow that we'd have air discharge.

178
00:27:03,940 --> 00:27:11,320
With the correct transformer at work, there'll be a slight smell of ozone.

179
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:21,300
If you turn off the light in the room, you'll see a slightly visible corona glow around this sphere.

180
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:22,600
Not more than that.

181
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:25,800
Somewhere there is the optimal mode.

182
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:29,800
A happy upcoming Old New Year to everyone.

183
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:32,280
Luck, happiness, love, prosperity.

184
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:34,300
Bye everyone!
